[EHV is a very nasty disease. Owners need to step up their biosecurity and get a notebook to document each animal's temperature twice daily. Treatment (which may be only supportive care) at the earliest moment may be important to the life of your animal. That earliest possible moment may be the 1st hint of a rise in body temperature. Do not blow off a tiny rise in temperature as ambient temperature. Be safe and treat early. Get your veterinarian involved at the earliest possible moment. Consider if that competition, show, trail ride, or whatever is so important that you would endanger your animal. This disease is nasty and shows no mercy. A few horses recover, but it is very few, and there are no guarantees yours may be in those very few recoveries. - Mod.TG

